==English==

===Etymology===
See [[w:The Gong Show|Wikipedia article on "The Gong Show"]].

===Noun===
'''[[gong]] [[show]]'''

# ''Contemporary Canadian and American English:'' An event that was a disaster, often in a way that is fun or memorable. (e.g. "Last night, we all went drinking, and the whole thing turned into a total gong show.")  Or, an initally serious event that went completely out of control (e.g. "That biology class was a gong show")